configset GLOBAL addr_allow_comments_after_route = VALUE
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Default Value: no
Data Type    : bool
Variable Type: addr
Apply to List: GLOBAL pseudo-list only
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

EXAMPLE:
configset GLOBAL addr_allow_comments_after_route = 1

(text above is from configshow, Mj2 0.1199902200, extracted 12 Apr 1999)


If this is true, Majordomo will allow addresses with comments after the <>
bracked route portion of an address.
This command, if set to a value of "1", allows "subscribe" commands
to be processed with technically illegal email addresses.

This is always legal:
   Joe Blow <joe@blow.com>

This is only accepted if "addr_allow_comments_after_route" is true:
   <joe@blow.com> Joe Blow

For a list of all help topics send this one-line message
   help topics
to the server at $MJ
